reviews.text: Very good quality Japanese food at very reasonable price. A meal for 3 can be between, HK$500-600 when you eat moderately.
Excellent food and fair price. Arrive early as line can take long.

Pros: pretty good rolls & cooked items, great dessert
Cons: Nigiri quality very average; the restaurant was out of my first two sake choices - including Hakkaisan. Table service was slow

My friend and I came in for a long lunch looking forward to trying Genki's "premium" option. We ran up a $1000 bill on lunch, but this will be unusual.  

Round 1 included soft shell crab temaki, agedashi tofu, and skewered pork belly. The temaki and tofu were excellent. While the pork was competently cooked, it lacked flavour.   The server informed me that the Hakkaisan was unavailable, to my great disappointment.  I ordered a small flask of an underwhelming daiginjo. 

Round two featured a variety of nigiri. The rice was fine, though the fish cutting was very "economy" style albeit at "proper restaurant" pricing.  The standing sushi bar  Sushi Tachi in TST & Mong Kok does a far better/more aesthetic cut. After an extended wait, our ordered hot sake first came out cold before being brought out hot after a second wait.

Round three of gluttony included a return of the soft shell crab temaki and a prawn tempura rice paper roll with mango sauce (utterly delicious).

A round of black sesame ice cream in a mochi crisp provided partial redemption. 

Overall impression: might come back for a much more limited roll-based lunch & ice cream, spending the serious dollars elsewhere. I'd rather go back to the cheaper Genki where our spending was much less for a similar gorge-a-thon or else spend marginally more at a proper sit-down restaurant (e.g. Nagomi @ the Harbour Grand HK) that adequately maintains their sake stock. This is a kaiten sushi experience pretending to be something more upmarket, if only in upmarket pricing.
Nice food, many people during lunch time. Reservation is recommended.
Nice Japanese restaurant which offers a large variety of sushi and Japanese food

reviews.text: 新鮮又美味👍👍👍👍
今晚6點45分用手機取位，7點左右便能入座了。魚生一流。

鍾意佢地嘅wasabi, 唔係一般用粉開果d。
野食比起元氣係高幾班嘅，價格雖然少少偏貴，但以質數嚟講可以接受。
服務一般。

reviews.text: It's an eye candy. There's a lot of high end brand, so make sure to bring a lot of money. One of the best place to have a shopping spree

The Time Square of Hong Kong, nice ambience with tons of stores! Movie theater, nice big supermarket nearby and a skip away from a wet mart. Literally has everything. They usually do seasonal events at the front which is pretty interesting.
Very popular shopping centre. Great place to spend time
Shopping center in Wan Chai. Not the fanciest of fanciest, but pretty good brands and not too busy.
The age is showing on the exterior, but the stores stay relevant. Still a great place to get all your shopping done.
